//question 
Design and develop a responsive website for an online Grocery Shop using JavaScript, PHP
and MySQL having 1) Home Page2) Login Page 3) Catalogue Page: 4) Registration Pag.
Create two tables: Consumer and Items

Run this SQL in your MySQL database:

sql
Copy
Edit
CREATE TABLE consumer (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(100),
    email VARCHAR(100),
    password VARCHAR(255)
);

CREATE TABLE items (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(100),
    price DECIMAL(10,2)
);
 Project Setup Instructions
1. Download & Extract
Download the project zip file:
ðŸ“¦ GroceryShop.zip

Extract it to your web server directory:

For XAMPP: C:\xampp\htdocs\GroceryShop

For WAMP: C:\wamp\www\GroceryShop

2. Start Apache and MySQL
Open XAMPP Control Panel

Click Start next to Apache and MySQL

3. Create Database and Tables
Open phpMyAdmin in your browser:
http://localhost/phpmyadmin

Click New, name your database: groceryshop, and click Create

Run the following SQL queries in the SQL tab:

sql
Copy
Edit
CREATE TABLE consumer (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(100),
    email VARCHAR(100),
    password VARCHAR(255)
);

CREATE TABLE items (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(100),
    price DECIMAL(10,2)
);

-- Optional: Insert sample items
INSERT INTO items (name, price) VALUES
('Rice', 45.00),
('Wheat Flour', 40.00),
('Milk', 25.00),
('Eggs (6 pack)', 30.00);
4. Run the Website
In your browser, go to:
ðŸ‘‰ http://localhost/GroceryShop

You will see the Home Page with links to:

Login

Register

Catalogue
